cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DM, cs.SI, cs.NE 

This paper discusses a problem with testing adaptive classifiers, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The issue of concept drift adaptation is also relevant to data mining (cs.DM) and signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the use of electricity benchmark data suggests a potential focus on neural networks (cs.NE) for time series analysis.
